<h2 id="expressions">Expressions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Ever since their return from their honeymoon, Fermina Daza had chosen her husband’s clothes according to the weather and the occasion, and <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="laid them out"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(把它们摆出来)</code></b> for him on a chair the night before so they would be ready for him when he came out of the bedroom.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>That was why she did not treat him like a difficult old man but as a senile baby, and that deception was providential for the two of them because it put them <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="beyond the reach of pity"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(不用被怜悯)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Wisdom comes to us when it can no longer do any good."><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(我们总是事后聪明，虽然届时已经毫无益处。)</code></b></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>She heard him awake with the roosters, and his first sign of life was a cough <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="without rhyme or reason"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(毫无道理)</code></b> that seemed intended to awaken her too.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>“Well I’ve bathed every day,” she shouted, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="beside herself"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(极度兴奋/发狂)</code></b> with rage, “and there’s always been soap.”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The impropriety shook the very foundations of the city, gave rise to slanders that were not easy to disprove, and was preserved in <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="popular tradition"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(地方流行)</code></b> as if it were a line from an operetta: “To hell the Archbishop!”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And it was not an <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="idle | lacking worth or basis - VAIN"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(毫无根据的)</code></b> threat.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>On some professional pretext or other he went to live in the interns’ <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="quarters"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(佣人或军人的宿舍、营房)</code></b> at Misericordia Hospitals, returning home only to change his clothes before making his evening house calls.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Then, fully awake, she remembered, and <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="tossed and turned"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(翻来覆去)</code></b> in fury with the world because in fact she had forgotten to replace the soap in the bathroom.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
